The paper focuses on geometric reasoning in the context of question-answering, which involves visual understanding and interpretation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper proposes a new deep network architecture for answering questions, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves natural language processing for question-answering, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes two synthetic benchmarks for evaluating geometric reasoning, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for developing new neural network architectures.
